The paper deals with privacy and encryption in cloud storage, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of ORAM schemes and block devices suggests a focus on data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The mention of sequential writing patterns and backend memory suggests a focus on computer architecture (cs.AR) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the testing and performance analysis of the proposed solution suggests a focus on systems and control (cs.SY).
